abstract: Fresh off a radical overhaul of its executive suite, Oracle posted better-than-expected results for its first quarter on the back of strong sales of new software products and higher maintenance and support revenue.
snippet: Fresh off a radical overhaul of its executive suite, Oracle posted better-than-expected results for its first quarter on the back of strong sales of new software products and higher maintenance and support revenue.
lead_paragraph: Fresh off a radical overhaul of its executive suite, Oracle told investors on Thursday that its house remained in order, Ashlee Vance writes in The New York Times.

headline.main: Oracle Profit Rises 20%, Higher Than Forecast
